description: A beaker-period barrow that was found to contain large amounts of deposited Iron Age and Roman material, interpreted as having been used as a shrine until at least the 4th CE.
bibliography: Beckensall, S G. “The Excavation of Money Mound.” Sussex Archaeological Collections 105 (2021): 1330. https://doi.org/10.5284/1085513.
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Money Mound, Hammerpond Road (West Sussex).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
